special
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:any of the rural recruits sworn in to control urban strikers, especially in the 1913 labour troubles (collectively also called Massey's Cossacks q.v.)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ?dateline -->in the 1932 riots We didn't know what a `Specials' were, but up and down Queen St were groups of men wearing white arm-bands and carrying clubs.
